An update to my previous xterm colors page, removed duplicates and fixed issues with two word colors. These colors are from the command &ldquo;showrgb&rdquo; and can be used for various X11 things. The primary spot I use them is for coloring the foreground/background in xterm.

Example:

<pre class="brush: plain; title: ; notranslate" title="">xterm -fg LightGoldenrod1 -bg CornflowerBlue
</pre>

You can View Source, Inspect Element or use a Color Picker to get the RGB values.

* * *
